cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NA, cs.MM 

The paper deals with visual recognition tasks, specifically representing images and videos with Symmetric Positive Definite (SPD) matrices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for handling high-dimensional SPD matrices, which involves optimization and learning, indicating that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses fast solutions for special cases, which suggests that it could belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several classification tasks, indicating that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
